    {
      "id": "6e8a9660eddffe8413ac266a4432218131aeaa2d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 143,
        "name": "Yang Sheng",
        "email": "ys@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ys"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-04 05:28:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSo, Looks like other place also need change to avoid such issue.\n\nIn  lustre/ptlrpc/ptlrpcd.c:\n\n        case PDB_POLICY_NEIGHBOR:\n#if defined(CONFIG_NUMA)\n        {\n                int i;\n                mask = *cpumask_of_node(cpu_to_node(index));\n                for (i = max; i < num_online_cpus(); i++)\n                        cpu_clear(i, mask);\n                pc->pc_npartners = cpus_weight(mask) - 1;\n                set_bit(LIOD_BIND, &pc->pc_flags);\n        }\n#else",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a3d429e1f4f73f846560c07e0964139672da3e2f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-01-04 14:24:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYang Sheng, I think it is different, ptlrpcd will check if node is online before calling cpumask_of_node, so it should be safe.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
